race.comment: METALLIC RULER (2) been around the mark at his three runs back, including latest fifth with the 60kg over 1400m at Sandown-Lakeside. Will relish the claim with the lugging bit going on and will prove hard to beat. TAI LUNG (3) retains his zest for racing and comes here in peak condition. Wound up strongly from midfield with an unlucky second over 1200m at Kembla Grange in BM64 class. Undefeated at this track and expected to go close. MAJOR TIME (1) faded late in his two runs back and should be close to his top for this. Claim helps again from the inside gate and will give a ton of cheek. FOURTH SPARGO (6) kept fresh and back to her preferred trip after struggling to run the 1200m out when ninth at Moruya in BM88 class. Key jockey change and shapes as a value prospect. CANI CANCAN (5) big drop in class after she failed to make an impression when eighth to Nazwah over 1000m at Warwick Farm in BM72 grade. Keep safe.
